schools.name: Centennial A School for Expeditionary Learning

data.description:
Welcome to this charming brick bungalow, a perfect blend of timeless elegance with modern updates. This Home has a 3.25% assumable fixed interest rate for qualified VA buyers. This delightful home features three bedrooms, one bath, original hardwood floors, and an updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances, offering a comfortable and stylish living experience.

As you step inside, you'll be greeted by the warmth and character of the original hardwood floors that flow throughout the home. The living area is bathed in natural light, creating a welcoming atmosphere for relaxation and entertaining. The updated kitchen boasts stainless steel appliances with room for a mobile island.

The three bedrooms offer comfort and privacy for the entire family. Each room is filled with natural light, complementing the warm tones of the original hardwood floors. 

Stepping outside, you'll discover a large backyard retreat with some creativity could provide additional income with an ADU or workshop or studio.

Situated in a sought-after neighborhood and close to I-70 for easy access to your mountain adventures! Within distance to notable Tennyson and hitting the links at Willis Case will be a breeze!
